ck\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Combine Lead Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,520],"id":"39ae2672-5c7d-f0e3-ad7d-05d12c62fb05","name":"Note: Warm → Drip via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cold → Park in Nurture List\n\nAppends a new row to 'Contact Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Combine Lead Paths · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,1000],"id":"3b381fd5-282e-8dd2-fe7e-5c7bd03d9dfd","name":"Note: Cold → Park in Nurture List"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Combine Lead Paths\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"b8ec06ea-d323-a4b1-23bc-d6d6ddc31203","name":"Note: Combine Lead Paths"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"b612c403-2e0d-26ae-51e5-ef4169e99405","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"510d885b-99ca-28ec-1110-200a508ddc8b","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per contact (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"1c628e9d-204f-6bb1-c786-01a201b749c6","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"59696ff8-a8f2-f12d-18f5-b7972bfe4b1f","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"02c38759-7806-dc06-a16c-34b11709437b","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"331cf607-8137-8816-fd77-c0731ca2e291","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"865c78ce-e360-5231-8a7d-3fb2c74588d0","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Load Previous Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"fda8714a-5831-972a-b1c0-0eda4332a44d","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nLooks up an existing HubSpot contact by last-modified date — finds records the pipeline hasn't processed yet.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 HubSpot private-app token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"57ff79e4-0e3b-fdd7-7367-3aea3b7547ea","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"4d5a37e5-88a7-becf-b02d-3f2db48f2ea9","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"fd0d3678-399d-fb50-24c6-2a14602b8808","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"87726227-580d-ae5d-10c7-2a8d263b1f1f","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty email","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"6c0f0146-88d3-66f0-2348-51c5ecbefcae","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty email\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"c9b3b8dd-b2e3-dd61-ee50-bb6dabbae957","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty email"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"16480e97-a992-004b-aef9-4d0a54a9e13f","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Contact Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"6b3a08e8-8248-b3f4-62cc-abdc2cfd0488","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10362,520],"id":"36887eae-512b-c847-40b5-81002ce93e38","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"fa13c513-5625-3e1c-0fe9-2a888d43e63e","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#sales`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,1540],"id":"95bd4a9c-802a-6d64-6b99-bec34755b933","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nCreates or updates a HubSpot contact by email — HubSpot is the CRM system of record for this pipeline.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 HubSpot private-app token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10362,1540],"id":"b8cc9738-768f-cfc5-e3a6-ed6ec0534cd3","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Route inbound leads with HubSpot and Slack on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Lead Capture & Routing · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nRoute inbound leads with HubSpot and Slack on autopilot. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual follow-ups is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Contact Form Submission → Stamp & Shape Contact → Payload Valid? → Score the Lead → Assign Round-Robin Owner → Route by Heat → Hot → HubSpot + Instant Ping → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to lead capture & routing without manual effort\n- Anyone automating follow-ups in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; HubSpot private-app token; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"80c596c3-e213-826e-63d6-e30c2aa22e0d","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nRound-robin owner assignment happens right after scoring, before routing — every lead gets an accountable owner regardless of tier, so even a 'cold' lead parked in the nurture list is someone's responsibility later, not an anonymous row in a spreadsheet.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"77cda7f6-df49-43db-0b22-0d1459d61f7b","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Change the hot/warm threshold values and watch the tier distribution shift.\n2. Add a 4th owner to the round-robin pool.\n3. Add a follow-up wait+check to the warm-drip branch, similar to the drip-ladder spine.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"06587e14-43bb-8a7e-e2eb-fa0e0e6b083b","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"114dbd5c-8884-0fd4-7e1e-41cd61050fd2","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"a84d248a-f4f0-2fe6-caa8-3c9e71a681ce","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your follow-ups process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"4825622b-3f9f-39be-3e76-61a1f829d67f","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"New Contact Form Submission":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Contact","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Contact":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Score the Lead","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Score the Lead":{"main":[[{"node":"Assign Round-Robin Owner","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Assign Round-Robin Owner":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Heat","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hot → HubSpot + Instant Ping":{"main":[[{"node":"Notify Assigned Owner","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Heat":{"main":[[{"node":"Hot → HubSpot + Instant Ping","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Warm → Drip via Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Cold → Park in Nurture List","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Notify Assigned Owner":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Lead Paths","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Warm → Drip via Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Lead Paths","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cold → Park in Nurture List":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Lead Paths","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Combine Lead Paths":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty email","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty email":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"New Contact Form Submission":[{"json":{"contactId":"CT-8801","email":"maria.gomez@northwind.io","company":"Northwind Traders","dealStage":"Proposal Sent"}},{"json":{"contactId":"CT-8802","email":"raj.patel@blueharbor.com","company":"Blue Harbor Logistics","dealStage":"Negotiation"}}]},"versionId":"9cee3f9d-3296-4910-